    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="608"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d608">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 31, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram received last night, regarding Lenz and missionary protection,
                    indicates a better spirit on the part of the Turkish Government than your
                    preceding telegram showed, and suggests that good management may avert proposed
                    formal demand for passports.<note n="1" xml:id="d608fn1">See telegram from Mr.
                        Terrell of October 30, 1895, printed on <ref target="#pg_1314">page
                            1314</ref>.</note> Impress firmly on Turkish Government our right to be
                    promptly answered as to just demands and our confidence that answers will be
                    satisfactory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
